txt.en: The Uruk roar defiantly.
'Rush the gates and drive those little maggots ahead, we've guests need slayin'!'
Private Instance: Urugarth
'Look lively! We've unwanted guests lookin' to be made into a meal!'
'This 'ill is too steep. We'll never get the seige equipment up it, we best keep them trolls 'appy.'
'We don't fight soon an' we'll start tearin' each other apart. Burn the towers to the ground we will!'
'Attack you worthless sods!'
'Quit your belly-achin' you maggot. You're bleatin' on like a stuck tark.'
Instance: Urugarth
'Off the tower you sack of filth! This be the providence of the Blogthop Tribe!'
'If we don't keep the trolls 'appy there'll be bigger problems then the seige equipment.'
'Let's just keep our 'eads down and make sure we don't end up whipped and strung up.'
'Why do you talk so much?'
'Everything looks okay up 'ere let's get back down the 'hill.'
'Quit your yammering, sod!'
'Keep your eyes on those towers. The boys is gettin' a bit ornery as of late.'
'I need to fight soon.'
'I'm not lying. I seen tarks, I'm sure of it.'
'Quiet down, curs! I 'eard a noise on the path!'
'It's 'ard to lose a troll. They're big. We should get back down the 'ill.'
The trolls bow their heads.
'I don't think makin' watch-towers makes any sense. What are we watchin' for anyway?'
'I 'eard that black liquid spreads fire faster than dry straw the tarks use for their 'omes.'
A deep rumbling growl emanates from the Warg.
'Keep the trolls 'appy. 'ow about we just keep the trolls?'
'I like these little servant things; later we should grab a couple and make then fight to the death.'
'Stand aside you maggots! I've recruits that need training.'
'Go back to standing around you sorry lot of vermin.'
'We're being attacked!'
'Let me here you boys yalp!'
'We've guests! Recruits, welcome them in.'
'Build towers, cook oil, make more powder. When will we get to fight?'
'Then we'd best get on with our search. Trolls! Kill anything not in our army.'
'Look at them, livin' under the roof like some bleeding tark.'
'Amarthiel gives us the worst lot she does. Look at all these 'ills.'
'Looks like their takin' a break again, eh?'
'It was tarks and the Wargs is all gone, look around.'
'You're a sorry lot ain't you? Keep in step you worms.'
'You'd best not be lying you worthless sack of filth.'
'No interruptions, I want these lads well trained. Keep everyone else out, understood?'
